Yes you should be skeptical - mainly because there are firewall products which do not live up
to their claims.  However, a proper firewall, complete with application gateways, a split
DNS, and intrusion detection on the gateway machine, should provide sufficient protection. 
That is, of course, if you disallow the most vulnerable services.

